                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.057,
                                "byte_start": 106496,
                                "byte_stop": 138783,
                                "text": "Justice Kagan has our opinion this morning in case 11-9540, Descamps versus United States."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.057,
                        "stop": 504.576,
                        "byte_start": 138783,
                        "byte_stop": 2124716,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15094,
                            "name": "Elena Kagan",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/elena_kagan",
                            "last_name": "Kagan",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2738,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1281157200,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Barack Obama",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2738"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32690,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 44456,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/elena-kagan-photo_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 1931,
                            "identifier": "elena_kagan"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.057,
                                "stop": 20.439,
                                "byte_start": 138783,
                                "byte_stop": 188312,
                                "text": "This is a case about a federal statute called ACCA, the Armed Career Criminal Act, possibly not what you\u0027re here for this morning."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.439,
                                "stop": 31.933,
                                "byte_start": 188312,
                                "byte_stop": 234287,
                                "text": "ACCA, we\u0027ve had many disagreements about ACCA over the years, I think one thing we would all agree on is that ACCA is not a very well written statute."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 31.933,
                                "stop": 40.826,
                                "byte_start": 234287,
                                "byte_stop": 269814,
                                "text": "And because it\u0027s not very well written, it\u0027s hard to apply and because it\u0027s hard to apply, it takes up a lot more of our time than we would like."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.826,
                                "stop": 42.204,
                                "byte_start": 269814,
                                "byte_stop": 275352,
                                "text": "So, what is ACCA?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 42.204,
                                "stop": 59.83,
                                "byte_start": 275352,
                                "byte_stop": 345882,
                                "text": "ACCA is a sentence enhancer. Certain people who are convicted of being a felon with a firearm that usually has a 10-year maximum sentence, but that sentence can get enhanced if the person has committed three violent felonies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.83,
                                "stop": 67.716,
                                "byte_start": 345882,
                                "byte_stop": 377438,
                                "text": "And it can get enhanced by quite a bit so that the sentence ends up, in this case, more than double what it otherwise would be."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.716,
                                "stop": 79.459,
                                "byte_start": 377438,
                                "byte_stop": 424354,
                                "text": "The question that ACCA often presents is how we figure out whether a prior felony is one of the three prior felonies that you can count under ACCA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 79.459,
                                "stop": 82.944,
                                "byte_start": 424354,
                                "byte_stop": 438356,
                                "text": "What the statute does is it lists a number of crimes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 82.944,
                                "stop": 86.36,
                                "byte_start": 438356,
                                "byte_stop": 451939,
                                "text": "It lists burglary and arson and extortion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 86.36,
                                "stop": 99.053,
                                "byte_start": 451939,
                                "byte_stop": 502721,
                                "text": "Who knows why those three and then it has something called a \u201cresidual clause\u201d, sort of a kitchen sink clause, which gives us a lot of difficulties too, but this case is about one of the listed crimes."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 99.053,
                                "stop": 103.464,
                                "byte_start": 502721,
                                "byte_stop": 520380,
                                "text": "It\u0027s about burglary and what you might think is, \u201cWell, that\u0027s pretty easy."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 103.464,
                                "stop": 117.601,
                                "byte_start": 520380,
                                "byte_stop": 576909,
                                "text": "All you have to do was look to see whether a person has been convicted of burglary and that gets counted as one of the three,\u201d what are called \u201cpredicate offenses,\u201d but in fact, it\u0027s not that easy for reasons that this case demonstrates."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.601,
                                "stop": 122.655,
                                "byte_start": 576909,
                                "byte_stop": 597180,
                                "text": "That is because different states define burglary very differently."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.655,
                                "stop": 135.759,
                                "byte_start": 597180,
                                "byte_stop": 649634,
                                "text": "So in some states, it\u0027s like the classic breaking and entering, and that we think is exactly the kind of violent felony that Congress meant to count as one of these three predicate offenses."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 135.759,
                                "stop": 142.232,
                                "byte_start": 649634,
                                "byte_stop": 675443,
                                "text": "But in some cases, in some states, burglary covers a much wider range of conduct."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 142.232,
                                "stop": 144.515,
                                "byte_start": 675443,
                                "byte_stop": 684638,
                                "text": "It also covers shoplifting."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 144.515,
                                "stop": 156.066,
                                "byte_start": 684638,
                                "byte_stop": 730823,
                                "text": "And we think actually that that\u0027s not the kind of thing that Congress meant to count to so greatly enhance peoples\u0027 sentences and that\u0027s what\u0027s true in this case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 156.066,
                                "stop": 167.397,
                                "byte_start": 730823,
                                "byte_stop": 776171,
                                "text": "The California burglary statute, which this case is about, defines burglary very widely to include not just breaking and entering but also to include shoplifting."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 167.397,
                                "stop": 172.335,
                                "byte_start": 776171,
                                "byte_stop": 795920,
                                "text": "And the question that we\u0027ve encountered is what to do with the statute like that."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 172.335,
                                "stop": 178.972,
                                "byte_start": 795920,
                                "byte_stop": 822460,
                                "text": "There are two approaches that you can follow: The first approach is called the \u201cfactual approach\u201d."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 178.972,
                                "stop": 180.427,
                                "byte_start": 822460,
                                "byte_stop": 828207,
                                "text": "Let\u0027s call it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 180.427,
                                "stop": 193.705,
                                "byte_start": 828207,
                                "byte_stop": 881392,
                                "text": "And that would involve looking to what the person actually did to try to figure out whether the person, in fact, did something that looks like breaking and entering or did something that looks like shoplifting."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 193.705,
                                "stop": 198.461,
                                "byte_start": 881392,
                                "byte_stop": 900409,
                                "text": "But we\u0027ve explained in many opinions that there are real problems with that approach."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 198.461,
                                "stop": 203.136,
                                "byte_start": 900409,
                                "byte_stop": 919113,
                                "text": "And the problems are, we don\u0027t think Congress meant for us to take that approach."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 203.136,
                                "stop": 209.42,
                                "byte_start": 919113,
                                "byte_stop": 944191,
                                "text": "We\u0027ve looked at the text of the ACCA statute and it seems as though that\u0027s not what Congress had in mind."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 209.42,
                                "stop": 222.073,
                                "byte_start": 944191,
                                "byte_stop": 994868,
                                "text": "We\u0027ve said that there are real constitutional problems with that approach as well because it would involve judges making determinations about what a defendant actually did, but in our system, properly belong to juries."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 222.073,
                                "stop": 239.799,
                                "byte_start": 994868,
                                "byte_stop": 1065712,
                                "text": "So we said that that\u0027s another problem with it and we\u0027ve said also that there are real practical problems with it because it\u0027s hard to figure out what somebody actually did sometimes many, many, years ago, many decades ago even, it\u0027s inefficient and it may very well be unfair."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 239.799,
                                "stop": 249.774,
                                "byte_start": 1065712,
                                "byte_stop": 1105627,
                                "text": "So, instead of adopting that approach, we\u0027ve adopted something called the \u201ccategorical approach\u201d and what we do is we figure out something that we called the \u201cgeneric crime of burglary\u201d."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 249.774,
                                "stop": 253.937,
                                "byte_start": 1105627,
                                "byte_stop": 1122346,
                                "text": "We say, \u201cWhat\u0027s mostly what burglary is?\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 253.937,
                                "stop": 259.843,
                                "byte_start": 1122346,
                                "byte_stop": 1145960,
                                "text": "And mostly, what burglary is and what we think Congress had in mind is breaking and entering."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 259.843,
                                "stop": 267.883,
                                "byte_start": 1145960,
                                "byte_stop": 1178039,
                                "text": "And then we compare the elements of that crime, the generic offence to the elements of the crime that the person was convicted of."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 267.883,
                                "stop": 281.078,
                                "byte_start": 1178039,
                                "byte_stop": 1230911,
                                "text": "So because -- if the person was convicted of a crime that\u0027s much broader than the generic offense, we\u0027ve said that that conviction cannot count under ACCA because we don\u0027t really know."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 281.078,
                                "stop": 294.904,
                                "byte_start": 1230911,
                                "byte_stop": 1286186,
                                "text": "The person might have been -- in fact actually committed breaking and entering or the person might have committed just shoplifting, and we don\u0027t to use the factual approach for all the reasons that I\u0027ve said."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 294.904,
                                "stop": 299.092,
                                "byte_start": 1286186,
                                "byte_stop": 1302904,
                                "text": "So, we basically just say that the conviction doesn\u0027t count under ACCA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 299.092,
                                "stop": 308.844,
                                "byte_start": 1302904,
                                "byte_stop": 1341879,
                                "text": "And that means that there are some criminals who get a break, but we\u0027ve decided that that\u0027s the better approach to take than the alternative."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 308.844,
                                "stop": 325.124,
                                "byte_start": 1341879,
                                "byte_stop": 1407080,
                                "text": "Now, what I\u0027ve said basically resolves this case because here, the defendant is named Michael Descamps and he was convicted for burglary under California law and the question is, \u201cCan that conviction count as an ACCA predicate offense?\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 325.124,
                                "stop": 329.075,
                                "byte_start": 1407080,
                                "byte_stop": 1422858,
                                "text": "And we \u2013 and -- the categorical approach would say, \u201cNo."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 329.075,
                                "stop": 339.694,
                                "byte_start": 1422858,
                                "byte_stop": 1465281,
                                "text": "It can\u0027t count because in California law, burglary includes all these non-violent things and so, it can\u0027t count, case closed.\u201d"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 339.694,
                                "stop": 344.865,
                                "byte_start": 1465281,
                                "byte_stop": 1485970,
                                "text": "Now, what the courts below did was that they said that the case was not closed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 344.865,
                                "stop": 368.749,
                                "byte_start": 1485970,
                                "byte_stop": 1581578,
                                "text": "They said that they could look beyond the elements of the crime that Mr. Descamps was convicted of, as long as it only considered certain generally reliable documents: Indictments, jury trial, jury charges, plea agreements, and plea colloquies to see what Mr. Descamps really did, to see whether he in fact broke and entered or just shoplifted."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 368.749,
                                "stop": 396.873,
                                "byte_start": 1581578,
                                "byte_stop": 1694009,
                                "text": "And looking to those documents is something that we, in fact, have approved in very limited situations and those limited situations are when the statute itself is something called \u201cdivisible,\u201d when it lists alternative crimes, you know crime X or crime Y or crime Z, and you\u0027re trying to figure out which crime the defendant was convicted of so that you can then compare that crime to the elements of the generic offense."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 396.873,
                                "stop": 401.439,
                                "byte_start": 1694009,
                                "byte_stop": 1712295,
                                "text": "I mean life is so much fun here under ACCA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 401.439,
                                "stop": 417.31,
                                "byte_start": 1712295,
                                "byte_stop": 1775825,
                                "text": "And so, we\u0027ve allowed courts to do this in that limited context where the statute lists crimes divisibly and we\u0027re just trying to figure out which crime the defendant was actually convicted of."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 417.31,
                                "stop": 423.124,
                                "byte_start": 1775825,
                                "byte_stop": 1799022,
                                "text": "But in this opinion, what we say is that that\u0027s the only context in which one can use that approach."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 423.124,
                                "stop": 425.959,
                                "byte_start": 1799022,
                                "byte_stop": 1810411,
                                "text": "It\u0027s called the \u201cmodified categorical approach\u201d."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 425.959,
                                "stop": 433.236,
                                "byte_start": 1810411,
                                "byte_stop": 1839459,
                                "text": "We say that that\u0027s the only context when a statute is divisible, but one can use a modified categorical approach."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 433.236,
                                "stop": 439.019,
                                "byte_start": 1839459,
                                "byte_stop": 1862656,
                                "text": "Otherwise, our standard categorical approach is what should work."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 439.019,
                                "stop": 461.836,
                                "byte_start": 1862656,
                                "byte_stop": 1953876,
                                "text": "And here because this statute did not list crimes divisibly, instead the statute had only a single set of elements that defined the relevant crime much more broadly than the generic offense, this statute flunks the categorical approach and so the conviction cannot be use as an act of predicate offense."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 461.836,
                                "stop": 492.053,
                                "byte_start": 1953876,
                                "byte_stop": 2074770,
                                "text": "We, basically, for reasons that are laid out in the opinion, show that the approach of the courts below, looking beyond the elements to try to figure out what the defendant actually did, would really just implode the categorical approach, and for all the reasons that we\u0027ve given, the categorical approach, although it sometimes leads to very peculiar results, is kind of the best way we can think of to make this statute work."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 492.053,
                                "stop": 494.424,
                                "byte_start": 2074770,
                                "byte_stop": 2084279,
                                "text": "So, the decision below is reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 494.424,
                                "stop": 501.443,
                                "byte_start": 2084279,
                                "byte_stop": 2112282,
                                "text": "Justice Kennedy has filed a concurring opinion and Justice Thomas has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 501.443,
                                "stop": 504.576,
                                "byte_start": 2112282,
                                "byte_stop": 2124716,
                                "text": "Justice Alito has filed a dissenting opinion."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
